 {"id":"beads_rust-1g8e","title":"Integrate rich output into dep subcommands","description":"## Command: br dep <add|rm|list|tree|cycles>

### Traffic Level: MEDIUM
Dependency management - needs visual graph representation.

### Current Implementation
Location: src/cli/commands/dep.rs
Subcommands: add, rm, list, tree, cycles

### Integration by Subcommand

#### dep add / dep rm
Simple confirmation with visual feedback:
```
✓ Added dependency: beads_rust-abc1 → beads_rust-def2
  beads_rust-abc1 now blocks beads_rust-def2
```

#### dep list
Table showing all dependencies for an issue:
```
╭─ Dependencies for beads_rust-abc1 ──────────────────╮
│                                                     │
│ Blocks (2):                                         │
│ ├── beads_rust-def2  [open]   Update login page     │
│ └── beads_rust-ghi3  [closed] Add unit tests        │
│                                                     │
│ Blocked by (1):                                     │
│ └── beads_rust-jkl4  [open]   Database migration    │
│                                                     │
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
```

#### dep tree
Use DependencyTree component for full graph:
```
beads_rust-abc1 [open] Fix authentication
├── blocks:
│   ├── beads_rust-def2 [open] Update login
│   │   └── beads_rust-ghi3 [open] Deploy
│   └── beads_rust-jkl4 [closed] Tests ✓
└── blocked-by:
    └── beads_rust-mno5 [in-progress] DB migration
```

#### dep cycles
Highlight cycle paths in red:
```
⚠ 1 dependency cycle detected:

  beads_rust-abc1 → beads_rust-def2 → beads_rust-ghi3 → beads_rust-abc1
  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

  Suggestion: Remove one of these dependencies to break the cycle.
```

### Status Indicators in Tree
- [open] - default color
- [in-progress] - yellow
- [closed] - dimmed + ✓
- Cycle node - red + ⚠

